  "duration": 186.67999267578125,
  "text": "I will hold on all the same, cause it's not outside I'm holding, it's the one who holds my name. Even faith like a mustard seed is faith enough to grow. I believe, help my unbelief, that's the only prayer I know. When the doubt rolls in like weather, I will hold on all the same, cause it's not outside I'm holding, it's the one who holds my name. I have stepped out on the water and I've felt myself go under, but a hand was always reaching through the lightning and the thunder. And the prayers I thought were silent, maybe they were always heard. So I'm leaning on a promise more than feeling more than word. Even faith like a mustard seed is faith enough to grow. I believe, help my unbelief, that's the only prayer I know. When the doubt rolls in like weather, I will hold on all the same, cause it's not outside I'm holding, it's the one who holds my name. When the doubt rolls in like weather, I will hold on all the same, cause it's not outside I'm holding, it's the one who holds my name. Oh, so I will hold on all the same, cause it's not outside I'm holding, it's the one who holds my name. Oh, so I'll keep a little faith alive, no bigger than a secret, and it's carried me this far, it is all I'll ever need.",
